authors: Daniel Stenberg and Contributors to the cURL project
description: curl/libcurl is an open source library for transferring data with URL syntax, supporting DICT, FILE, FTP, FTPS, Gopher, HTTP, HTTPS, IMAP, IMAPS, LDAP, LDAPS, POP3, POP3S, RTMP, RTSP, SCP, SFTP, SMB, SMTP, SMTPS, Telnet and TFTP. curl supports SSL certificates, HTTP POST, HTTP PUT, FTP uploading, HTTP form based upload, proxies, HTTP/2, cookies, user+password authentication (Basic, Plain, Digest, CRAM-MD5, NTLM, Negotiate and Kerberos), file transfer resume, proxy tunneling and more.
releaseNotes:
This is a cURL library package in dynamic linkage. Build notes:
			Version: 7.45.0
			Toolset: v140.
			SSL lib: OpenSSL.
			Compression lib: zlib.
			Calling convention: cdecl.
			Debug information: Program Database (/Zi).
			ZLib: yes.
			OpenSSL: yes.
			LibSSH2: yes.
			Package splitting: off ( non CoApp overlay, Please read https://github.com/coapp/coapp.powershell/issues/116 ).
			Author: Kyselgov Evgeny (kyselgov@gmail.com).
summary: cURL and libcurl is a free client-side URL transfer library, supporting all main protocols of transferring data.
title: cURL transferring data library
